        {
            "Original": "It is RECOMMENDED to set short lifetimes, typically shorter than TEMP_VALID_LIFETIME and TEMP_PREFERRED_LIFETIME (see [Section 5 of [RFC4941]](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4941#section-5)).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A DHCP server implementation MAY generate temporary addresses, referring to the algorithm defined in [Section 3.2.1 of [RFC4941]](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4941#section-3.2.1), with the additional condition that any new address is not the same as any assigned address.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The server MAY update the DNS for a temporary address, as described in [Section 4 of [RFC4941]](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4941#section-4).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "On the clients, by default, temporary addresses are preferred in source address selection, according to Rule 7 in [Section 5 of [RFC6724]](https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc6724#section-5).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "However, this policy can be overridden.",
            "Adjusted": "However, the policy of preferring temporary addresses in source address selection can be overridden."
