        },
        {
            "Original": "A 4-octet field containing an unsigned integer.",
            "Adjusted": "IAID is a 4-octet field containing an unsigned integer."
        },
        {
            "Original": "T1 The time interval after which the client should contact the server from which the addresses in the IA_NA were obtained to extend the lifetimes of the addresses assigned to the IA_NA; T1 is a time duration relative to the current time expressed in units of seconds.",
            "Adjusted": "T1 is the time interval after which the client should contact the server from which the addresses in the IA_NA were obtained to extend the lifetimes of the addresses assigned to the IA_NA; T1 is a time duration relative to the current time expressed in units of seconds."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A 4-octet field containing an unsigned integer.",
            "Adjusted": "T1 is a 4-octet field containing an unsigned integer."
        },
        {
            "Original": "T2 The time interval after which the client should contact any available server to extend the lifetimes of the addresses assigned to the IA_NA; T2 is a time duration relative to the current time expressed in units of seconds.",
            "Adjusted": "T2 is the time interval after which the client should contact any available server to extend the lifetimes of the addresses assigned to the IA_NA; T2 is a time duration relative to the current time expressed in units of seconds."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A 4-octet field containing an unsigned integer.",
            "Adjusted": "T2 is a 4-octet field containing an unsigned integer."
        },
        {
            "Original": "IA_NA-options Options associated with this IA_NA.",
            "Adjusted": "IA_NA-options are options associated with this IA_NA."
        },
        {
            "Original": "A variable-length field (12 octets less than the value in the option-len field).",
            "Adjusted": "IA_NA-options is a variable-length field (12 octets less than the value in the option-len field)."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The IA_NA-options field encapsulates those options that are specific to this IA_NA.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For example, all of the IA Address options (see Section 21.6) carrying the addresses associated with this IA_NA are in the IA_NA-options field.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Each IA_NA carries one \"set\" of non-temporary addresses; it is up to the server policy to determine how many addresses are assigned, but typically at most one address is assigned from each prefix assigned to the link to which the client is attached.",
            "Adjusted": "Each IA_NA carries one \"set\" of non-temporary addresses; server policy determines how many addresses are assigned, but typically at most one address is assigned from each prefix assigned to the link to which the client is attached."
        },
        {
            "Original": "An IA_NA option may only appear in the options area of a DHCP message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A DHCP message may contain multiple IA_NA options (though each must have a unique IAID).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The status of any operations involving this IA_NA is indicated in a Status Code option (see Section 21.13) in the IA_NA-options field.",
